title: Abbott warns Taylor against making Liberal party ‘One Nation-lite’ | ABC NEWS
description: Angus Taylor has vowed changes to the Liberal party in his first remarks as the party’s new leader, highlighting the Coalition’s position on Labor’s personal income tax and immigration standards.  Former prime minister Tony Abott has warned Mr Taylor against being ‘One Nation-lite’ or ‘teal-lite’, as the Coalition faces fierce challenges from Pauline Hanson’s party and teal independents for votes.  Angus Taylor took over the party from deposed leader Sussan Ley. title: German chancellor slams NATO's over-reliance on US | ABC NEWS
description: World leaders are gathering at the Munich Security Conference to discuss the future of NATO, Greenland and the Ukraine war.  German Chancellor Friedrich Merz blamed European nations for over-reliance on the US military.  US Secretary of State Marco Rubio is set to address the conference on President Donald Trump’s behalf, as Europe speculates Washington’s stance on global security issues. title: Two men jailed for life after plotting terror attack on UK Jewish community | ABC NEWS
description: Two men have been sentenced to life in prison in the UK for attempting to carry out what could have been the country’s deadliest terror attack. Walid Saadaoui and Amar Hussein pledged their allegiance to the Islamic State (IS) and were planning an attack on England’s Jewish community.  UK police thwarted their plot with the help of an undercover officer and arrested both men. title: Two killed in car crash after police pursuit in Sydney’s south-west | ABC NEWS
description: A car crash has killed two innocent bystanders after a police pursuit in Sydney’s south-west. Police began chasing a vehicle which was reportedly stolen in South Hurstville, but dangerous conditions forced them to abandon the chase and track the car along the M5 motorway by helicopter.  The driver was arrested after allegedly fleeing the scene on Old Hume Highway in Camden South. title: Scotty James becomes first Aussie to win three medals at Winter Olympics | ABC NEWS
description: "I'd love to go to the games in France and I don't see why trying again in four years is not a big ask." Five-time Olympian Scotty James spoke with ABC Sport’s Erin Marsicovetere following his silver medal performance in the Men’s Snowboard Halfpipe, saying he’s already thinking about returning for the French Alps 2030 in the hopes of securing Olympic gold.
